resources.description: Send alerts - when major issues arise - on PagerDuty

metadata.longDescription: With PagerDuty, you can receive alerts from your tools. (The PagerDuty integration feature is not created by, affiliated with, or supported by PagerDuty, Inc).  [Create an account at pagerduty.com](https://signup.pagerduty.com/accounts/new)

site_name.title: PagerDuty site name
site_name.description: Your PagerDuty site name is the prefix of your PagerDuty website; for example, https://site-name.pagerduty.com.

api_key.title: API access key
api_key.description: Type your API access key. You can find or create this key in the Configuration/API Access section of the PagerDuty website. [PagerDuty Support article on how to get API Key](https://support.pagerduty.com/hc/en-us/articles/202829310-Generating-an-API-Key).

service_name.title: PagerDuty service name
service_name.description: Type the name of the PagerDuty service to post alerts to. If you want alerts to be posted to a new service, type a new name. PagerDuty will create the service.

user_email.title: Primary contact email
user_email.description: Type the email of the primary user to be contacted when an alert is posted. If you want alerts to be sent to a new email, type a new email. PagerDuty will create the new user.

user_phone.title: Primary contact phone number
user_phone.description: Type the phone number of the primary user to be contacted when an alert is posted. Phone number should include national code follow by space and 10 digit number - i.e. +1 1234567890 - if the national code is omitted, default is set to +1. PagerDuty will create the appropriate contact information with the phone number if needed.
